    <h1>The Logic of Scientific Discovery</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Karl Popper · 1934 (German), 1959 (English) · Routledge · <a href="https://archive.org/details/logicofscientifi0000popp">Internet Archive</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">You cannot prove a theory, only disprove it. Falsifiability is the line between science and non-science. A theory that forbids nothing explains nothing.</p>
    </div>

